node.text:
Recipes below👩🏻‍🍳 Chicken, Prawns, Salmon.. Which is your favorite?!😍

All dishes approximately 500 CALORIES
⠀
⠀
🍗CHICKEN🍗
mac n’ cheese
(the coziest of cozy comfort food, amiright?), paired it with cast iron-cooked lemon-honey-garlic-sage chicken + grilled broccolini for a noodle night done right 💯☺️ macaroni & cheese •• lemon honey garlic sage chicken 🌿🍋 •• grilled broccoli parmesan & red pepper 🥦
⠀
⠀

🍤 PRAWNS 🍤
🔥SPICY Garlic Cajun Shrimp
Almond flour fettuccine tossed in olive oil, dried basil, dried sage, and parmesan •• grilled asparagus w/ parmesan.

🍣SALMON🍣
with hasselback potatoes.
HOW TO MAKE THE PERFECT CRISPY SALMON:
Honey garlic chipotle salmon 1) combine 1 tbsp honey, 1/4 tsp. chipotle chili powder, 1 tbsp. melted butter, s+p. Spread over two 4-6 oz. fillets 2) in a pan, heat 1 tsp oil; add salmon, skin side up, and sear for 3 mins; flip, and cook an additional 3-4 mins •• crispy garlic-parmesan hasselback potato •• grilled asparagus w/ parmesan and red pepper.
⠀
⠀
Which is your favourite protein?
Salmon is always a winner for me:)

node.text:
Broccoli rice
By @feelgoodfoodie
.
INGREDIENTS
For the broccoli rice
4 cups broccoli florets about 2 small crowns
1 tablespoon olive oil
1 garlic clove, minced
1 green onion thinly sliced, white and green parts separated
For the Sauce
¼ cup hoisin sauce
¼ cup water
1 tablespoons cornstarch
1 tablespoon soy sauce
1 tablespoon toasted sesame seed oil
1 teaspoon fresh ginger, minced
For the beef
1 tablespoon olive oil
1 pound flank steak, thinly sliced across the grain
Salt and pepper, to taste
.
INSTRUCTIONS
1. To make the riced broccoli, process the broccoli florets in a blender or food processor until you get a riced texture. Heat a pan with olive oil on medium, add the garlic and the white parts of the green onions and fry until fragrant, about 1-2 minutes. Add the riced broccoli to the mixture and toss together until the broccoli slightly softens, about 2-4 minutes. Divide the broccoli between 4 bowls and wipe clean the pan with a paper towel
2. To make the sauce, whisk together the ingredients in a small bowl or a small blender. Set aside.
3. To cook the steak, season with salt and pepper. Then heat the pan used for broccoli rice with olive oil on medium-high. Place the steak strips on the pan in a single layer and cook for 1-2 minutes per side to brown each steak strip. You many need to cook in batches. Add the sauce to the steak and reduce the heat to low. Cook for an additional 3-5 minutes, stirring to coat and allowing the sauce to thicken.
4. Serve the steak on top of the riced broccoli, and garnish with the green parts of the green onions and red pepper flakes.
.
#healthyfood #broccoli #rice #lowcarb #lowcalories #realfood

3 healthy + easy Breakfast Ideas! Recipes below👩🏻‍🍳 1-3, Which is your favourite?!😍💫

By @sara.haven ❤️
⠀
All dishes approximately 500 CALORIES 💫
⠀
⠀
🥕 VEGGIE PLATE 🥕
Roasted honey-garlic-sriracha carrots🙌🏻 (toss in melted garlic ghee, manuka honey, and sriracha; roast at 400 F for ~20 mins); broiled campari tomatoes; sunny fried egg; sautéed garlicky spinach & cremini mushrooms sprinkled with parmesan
⠀
🍌 BANANA PALEO 🍌
Mini Paleo Banana 🍌 Pancakes 🥞 using 2 eggs 1 banana •• sautéed spinach w/ red pepper + parmesan 🍃•• crispy egg •• organic raspberries •• avocado w/ ‘everything but the bagel’ seasoning🥯
⠀
🥜 NUT BUTTER COMBO 🥜
Crispy egg •• fresh baby tomatoes •• toast 2 ways nut butter and avo •• spinach w/ parmesan
⠀
⠀
Which would be your favourite?!
Pancakes are always a winner for me :)

node.text:
Follow 👉 @bodysmartfitness for the best nutrition, mindset and fitness tips.
.
4 healthy and tasty meals 😍. Which one is your favorite? 😋 1,2,3 or 4?👇
-
✔️ SAVE this Post to make later
✔️ TAG a friend who needs this #healthyeating inspo
✔️ FOLLOW @calories.tips for daily #cleaneating inspo & recipes from across the gram
-
📸 @choosing_balance
-
1.Leftover blackened shrimp 🍤 easy frozen stir fried veggies heated over medium heat for 6-8 minutes (I thaw them beforehand) with coconut aminos added to them. Sooo tasty 😍😍 2.1 piece of salmon with a sprinkle of garlic powder, pepper, salt, and lemon 🍋 squeezed on it cooked over medium heat for 3 mins on each side (get the pan hot first and add olive oil) + sautéed zoodles cooked for 3-4 mins over low medium heat in olive oil + 1/2 avocado 🥑

3.1 piece of skillet chicken leftover from a few meals ago (recipe a few posts back!) + easy broiled sweet potatoes 🍠 + 1/2 avocado 🥑 + tomatoes 🍅

4.leftover @eatbanza chickpea pasta 🍝 with 1 tbsp of avocado oil + 1 tsp garlic powder + 1 tsp onion powder + sprinkle of red pepper flakes + leftover shrimp 🍤 with @primalpalate new bae seasoning + sautéed mushrooms and spinach + 1/2 avocado 🥑

VEGAN & GLUTEN FREE! 3 INGREDIENT EVERYTHING POTATO CHIPS with GUAC 🥑 by @peanutbutterandjillybeans 
...
 30 Minutes • 124 Calories • Easy • Oven-Baked & CRISPY!
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
This is a healthy snack that will take you 30 MINUTES to whip up anytime!...
 
📝 Ingredients 
* 2 cups thinly sliced red potatoes

* 4 tbsp Everything Seasoning

* Olive oil or Avocado Oil Spray
 
👩‍🍳 Instructions ⠀⠀
 
1️⃣ Preheat oven to 450 Degrees. Slice potatos as thin as you can get them (about 1/8th of an inch).
 
2️⃣ Line a baking sheet with parchment paper or foil, and spray with olive oil spray. You can also use a wire baking rack! Lay the potatoes onto the baking sheet and spray with oil. Season generously with everything seasoning. Bake for 30 minutes or until desired crispiness! 
 
3️⃣ Serve with your favorite dipping sauce!

This Grilled Chili Lime Shrimp Salad really hit the spot. Fresh and flavorful perfect for a hot summer day! By @zestmylemon
.
Here’s how I made it:
.
Add some peeled and deveined shrimp to a bowl. Toss with olive oil, chili lime seasoning, garlic powder and fresh lime juice. Prepare a grill or heat a grill pan. Place shrimp on grill and cook on each side for 3-4 minutes until pink and lightly charred. In a skillet on the stovetop heat 1 tablespoon of olive oil. Add 1 cup cooked corn kernels and season with chili lime seasoning. Cook the corn in the pan stirring occasionally until it becomes golden and toasty. In a large bowl add some chopped romaine lettuce. Top with charred corn, grilled shrimp, cherry tomatoes, avocado and minced red onion. Drizzle in some extra virgin olive oil and squeeze in some fresh lime juice. Season with sea salt and garnish with fresh chopped cilantro. It’s so darn tasty. Hope you’re having an amazing day!

Who needs a delicious dinner idea for tonight? 🙋‍♀️🍽 
 
Baked Honey Mustard Salmon recipe is so easy to make and ready to serve in just under 30 minutes. 
 
This salmon filet recipe by @healthyfitnessmeals is so healthy, moist, delicious, and oven-baked to perfection. Perfect for a busy weeknight dinner. 
 
📝Ingredients
1 pound salmon fillet skin-on
1 large lemon
1 tbsp. finely chopped fresh parsley optional for garnishing 1 tbsp. coconut oil melted 2 tbsp. honey 3 tbsp. whole Dijon mustard 2 tbsp. lemon juice 1/2 tsp. kosher salt or to taste 1/4 tsp. freshly ground black pepper or to taste

🧑‍🍳 Instructions
1. Preheat the oven to 375°F.

2. Whisk all the sauce ingredients to a bowl and set aside. Slice the lemon into thin rounds and finely chop the parsley. 
3. Add a layer of sliced lemon into a baking dish. Place the salmon on top. 
4. Pour 2/3rd of the sauce over the salmon. Rub until well coated. Bake for 12 minutes, or until salmon is cooked through. 
5. Pour the remaining 1/3rd cup of the sauce and broil for about 2-3 minutes more, until nicely golden brown. 
6. Garnish with chopped parsley and serve.
 
#salmon #salmondinner #dinner #healthyeats #fishdinner #mediterraneandiet #mediterraneanfood #lemons #nutrition #dietplan
